OL,6,FWith members of several unions having
OL,7,Falready voted in favour of strike
OL,8,Faction if the impasse is not resolved,
OL,9,Fthere now appears an increased
OL,10,Fprospect of teachers taking to the
OL,11,Fpicket line if a breakthrough is not
OL,12,Fachieved in the near future.
OL,14,FWhile members of one of the unions
OL,15,Frepresented by the NITC, the National
OL,16,FUnion of Head Teachers, did back the
OL,17,Fdeal, the other unions rejected it `
OL,18,Fmeaning the collective position of the
OL,19,Fcouncil is not to approve ratification.
